            {
              "id": "NonThreadSafeSingleton",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "Singleton is not thread safe"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "\nNon-thread safe singletons can result in bad state changes. Eliminate\nstatic singletons if possible by instantiating the object directly. Static\nsingletons are usually not needed as only a single instance exists anyway.\nOther possible fixes are to synchronize the entire method or to use an\n[initialize-on-demand holder class](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Initialization-on-demand_holder_idiom).\n\nRefrain from using the double-checked locking pattern. The Java Memory Model doesn't\nguarantee it to work unless the variable is declared as `volatile`, adding an unneeded\nperformance penalty. [Reference](http://www.cs.umd.edu/~pugh/java/memoryModel/DoubleCheckedLocking.html)\n\nSee Effective Java, item 48.\n        "
              },
              "helpUri": "https://docs.pmd-code.org/snapshot/pmd_rules_java_multithreading.html#nonthreadsafesingleton",
              "help": {
                "text": "\nNon-thread safe singletons can result in bad state changes. Eliminate\nstatic singletons if possible by instantiating the object directly. Static\nsingletons are usually not needed as only a single instance exists anyway.\nOther possible fixes are to synchronize the entire method or to use an\n[initialize-on-demand holder class](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Initialization-on-demand_holder_idiom).\n\nRefrain from using the double-checked locking pattern. The Java Memory Model doesn't\nguarantee it to work unless the variable is declared as `volatile`, adding an unneeded\nperformance penalty. [Reference](http://www.cs.umd.edu/~pugh/java/memoryModel/DoubleCheckedLocking.html)\n\nSee Effective Java, item 48.\n        "
              },
              "properties": {
                "ruleset": "Multithreading",
                "priority": 3,
                "tags": [
                  "Multithreading"
                ]
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "warning"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "UnnecessaryFullyQualifiedName",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "Unnecessary qualifier 'JabRefGuiPreferences': 'singleton' is already in scope because it is declared in an enclosing type"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "\nImport statements allow the use of non-fully qualified names.  The use of a fully qualified name\nwhich is covered by an import statement is redundant.  Consider using the non-fully qualified name.\n        "
              },
              "helpUri": "https://docs.pmd-code.org/snapshot/pmd_rules_java_codestyle.html#unnecessaryfullyqualifiedname",
              "help": {
                "text": "\nImport statements allow the use of non-fully qualified names.  The use of a fully qualified name\nwhich is covered by an import statement is redundant.  Consider using the non-fully qualified name.\n        "
              },
              "properties": {
                "ruleset": "Code Style",
                "priority": 4,
                "tags": [
                  "Code Style"
                ]
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "note"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "MethodArgumentCouldBeFinal",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "Parameter 'path' is not assigned and could be declared final"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "\n            Reports method and constructor parameters that can be made final because they are never reassigned within the body of the method.\n\n            This rule ignores unused parameters so as not to overlap with the rule {% rule java/bestpractices/UnusedFormalParameter %}.\n            It will also ignore the parameters of abstract methods.\n        "
              },
              "helpUri": "https://docs.pmd-code.org/snapshot/pmd_rules_java_codestyle.html#methodargumentcouldbefinal",
              "help": {
                "text": "\n            Reports method and constructor parameters that can be made final because they are never reassigned within the body of the method.\n\n            This rule ignores unused parameters so as not to overlap with the rule {% rule java/bestpractices/UnusedFormalParameter %}.\n            It will also ignore the parameters of abstract methods.\n        "
              },
              "properties": {
                "ruleset": "Code Style",
                "priority": 3,
                "tags": [
                  "Code Style"
                ]
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "warning"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "OnlyOneReturn",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "A method should have only one exit point, and that should be the last statement in the method"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "\nA method should have only one exit point, and that should be the last statement in the method.\n        "
              },
              "helpUri": "https://docs.pmd-code.org/snapshot/pmd_rules_java_codestyle.html#onlyonereturn",
              "help": {
                "text": "\nA method should have only one exit point, and that should be the last statement in the method.\n        "
              },
              "properties": {
                "ruleset": "Code Style",
                "priority": 3,
                "tags": [
                  "Code Style"
                ]
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "warning"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "MethodArgumentCouldBeFinal",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "Parameter 'defaults' is not assigned and could be declared final"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "\n            Reports method and constructor parameters that can be made final because they are never reassigned within the body of the method.\n\n            This rule ignores unused parameters so as not to overlap with the rule {% rule java/bestpractices/UnusedFormalParameter %}.\n            It will also ignore the parameters of abstract methods.\n        "
              },
              "helpUri": "https://docs.pmd-code.org/snapshot/pmd_rules_java_codestyle.html#methodargumentcouldbefinal",
              "help": {
                "text": "\n            Reports method and constructor parameters that can be made final because they are never reassigned within the body of the method.\n\n            This rule ignores unused parameters so as not to overlap with the rule {% rule java/bestpractices/UnusedFormalParameter %}.\n            It will also ignore the parameters of abstract methods.\n        "
              },
              "properties": {
                "ruleset": "Code Style",
                "priority": 3,
                "tags": [
                  "Code Style"
                ]
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "warning"
              }
            },
            {
              "id": "UseConcurrentHashMap",
              "shortDescription": {
                "text": "If you run in Java5 or newer and have concurrent access, you should use the ConcurrentHashMap implementation"
              },
              "fullDescription": {
                "text": "\nSince Java5 brought a new implementation of the Map designed for multi-threaded access, you can\nperform efficient map reads without blocking other threads.\n        "
              },
              "helpUri": "https://docs.pmd-code.org/snapshot/pmd_rules_java_multithreading.html#useconcurrenthashmap",
              "help": {
                "text": "\nSince Java5 brought a new implementation of the Map designed for multi-threaded access, you can\nperform efficient map reads without blocking other threads.\n        "
              },
              "properties": {
                "ruleset": "Multithreading",
                "priority": 3,
                "tags": [
                  "Multithreading"
                ]
              },
              "defaultConfiguration": {
                "level": "warning"
              }
            },
